36 (5) Health services facility. – A facility that is licensed under (i) Chapter 131E or
37 Chapter 122C of the General Statutes or (ii) the licensing laws of another state
38 for the provision of the same services in the ordinary course of business or
39 practice as would require the facility to be licensed under Chapter 131E or
40 Chapter 122C of the General Statutes were the facility located in this State.
41 (6) Healthcare provider. – A health services facility or a person who is licensed,
42 registered, or certified under Chapter 90 or Chapter 90B of the General
43 Statutes, or under the laws of another state, to provide healthcare services in
44 the ordinary care of business or practice, or as a profession, or in an approved
45 education or training program.
46 (7) Reserved for future codification purposes.
47 (8) Insurer. – As defined in G.S. 58-3-167.
48 "§ 90-704. Billing for certain breast cancer prevention services.
